WEBVTT

00:01.835 --> 00:03.086
{\an8}♪ HER HEART IS BRIGHT ♪

00:03.169 --> 00:04.713
{\an8}♪ SHE'S NELLA
THE PRINCESS KNIGHT ♪

00:04.796 --> 00:08.007
{\an7}♪ ADVENTURE IS CALLING,
SHE CAN'T STAY AWAY ♪

00:08.090 --> 00:11.428
{\an7}♪ HER ARMOR IS SPARKLING,
HER COURAGE IS GREAT ♪

00:11.511 --> 00:14.764
{\an7}♪ HER NECKLACE IS GLOWING,
NOW SHE'LL FIND A WAY ♪

00:14.848 --> 00:16.933
{\an7}♪ WITH HELP FROM
HER BEST FRIENDS ♪

00:17.016 --> 00:18.935
{\an8}♪ THEY'LL SAVE THE DAY ♪

00:19.018 --> 00:20.520
{\an8}♪ HER HEART IS BRIGHT ♪

00:20.603 --> 00:22.605
{\an8}♪ SHE'S NELLA
THE PRINCESS KNIGHT ♪

00:22.689 --> 00:26.276
{\an7}♪ TRUE TO HERSELF,
DOING WHAT'S RIGHT ♪

00:26.359 --> 00:27.610
{\an8}♪ HER HEART IS BRIGHT ♪

00:27.694 --> 00:30.864
{\an8}♪ SHE'S NELLA
THE PRINCESS KNIGHT ♪

00:32.031 --> 00:34.492
{\an8}"PRINCESS NELLA'S ORCHESTRA."

00:35.869 --> 00:37.620
[ROYAL FANFARE]

00:37.704 --> 00:39.748
[APPLAUSE]

00:40.999 --> 00:43.168
OH, BOY,
I LOVE A SHOW!

00:43.251 --> 00:45.587
{\an1}SHH.
CLOD, IT'S STARTING!

00:45.670 --> 00:49.215
OH, BOY, I LOVE IT
WHEN A SHOW STARTS!

00:49.299 --> 00:50.425
HELLO, EVERYONE!

00:50.508 --> 00:52.177
I'M
PRINCESS NELLA,

00:52.260 --> 00:54.262
AND WELCOME TO
THE FIRST ANNUAL

00:54.345 --> 00:56.139
ROYAL CONCERT
IN THE WOODS.

00:56.222 --> 01:00.268
WE'VE BEEN WORKING EXTRA HARD
ON AN EXTRAORDINARY NEW SONG.

01:00.351 --> 01:02.896
{\an8}TRINKET,
IF YOU PLEASE?

01:02.979 --> 01:04.563
[PITCH PIPE PLAYING]

01:04.647 --> 01:08.485
ALL: ♪ WE SING THIS SONG
FOR YOU ♪

01:08.568 --> 01:12.489
[LOUD HOWLING]

01:15.116 --> 01:17.035
ORC!

01:17.118 --> 01:18.578
CRITTER: HERE HE COMES!

01:18.661 --> 01:19.662
CRITTER #2: RUN!

01:19.746 --> 01:20.705
{\an1}WHOA!

01:20.789 --> 01:22.582
WHOA!
GOT IT!

01:22.665 --> 01:24.501
{\an5}CRITTER: WHOA!

01:22.665 --> 01:24.501
CRITTER #2: OOPSIE!

01:24.584 --> 01:26.836
[SCREAMING]

01:27.837 --> 01:29.672
EVERYBODY, IT'S OK!
HE'S GONE!

01:29.756 --> 01:33.134
REALLY?

01:29.756 --> 01:33.134
ARE YOU SURE?

01:33.218 --> 01:34.260
GREAT SHOW, GUYS!

01:34.344 --> 01:37.847
{\an5}LOVED THE ENDING
WITH THE ORC.
WHAT A TWIST.

01:37.931 --> 01:41.434
{\an5}UM, I DON'T THINK
THAT WAS SUPPOSED
TO HAPPEN, BUDDY.

01:41.518 --> 01:43.019
TRINKET: OF COURSE NOT!

01:43.102 --> 01:44.312
BECAUSE OF
THAT ORC,

01:44.395 --> 01:45.772
NO ONE WAS ABLE
TO HEAR ME SING.

01:45.855 --> 01:46.606
[GASPING]

01:46.689 --> 01:49.484
{\an1}HOW DISAPPOINTED
THEY MUST BE!

01:49.567 --> 01:51.361
YEAH, HE TRIED
TO SCARE US AWAY,

01:51.444 --> 01:53.154
AND WE HAD TO STOP
THE SHOW.

01:53.238 --> 01:55.114
I WONDER WHAT
MADE HIM DO THAT.

01:55.198 --> 01:57.742
{\an5}OOH, OOH, LET ME
CHECK MY KNIGHTLY
TRADING CARDS!

01:57.826 --> 02:00.453
{\an1}THEY TELL ME EVERYTHING
A YOUNG KNIGHT NEEDS TO KNOW!

02:00.537 --> 02:01.871
UH, LET'S SEE.

02:01.955 --> 02:04.874
IT SAYS RIGHT HERE THAT ORCS
LIKE MUCK AND MUD,

02:04.958 --> 02:06.334
THEY EAT BUGS,

02:06.417 --> 02:08.711
OOH, AND THEY'RE EXCELLENT
ROLLER SKATERS!

02:08.794 --> 02:10.213
{\an5}GARRETT: AND--

02:08.794 --> 02:10.213
ALL: GARRETT!

02:10.295 --> 02:12.298
OOH, UH, SORRY.
[GASPING]

02:12.382 --> 02:15.552
{\an4}IT SAYS THAT ORCS
LIVE RIGHT AROUND
THIS PART OF THE WOODS.

02:15.635 --> 02:18.263
OH, WE WERE SINGING
NEAR HIS HOME.

02:18.346 --> 02:19.222
GUESS HE DIDN'T
LIKE THAT.

02:19.305 --> 02:21.724
OH, WELL.
THAT'S THE END OF THAT.

02:21.808 --> 02:23.143
BETTER LUCK NEXT YEAR,
GUYS.

02:23.226 --> 02:25.311
OUR CHORUS CAN'T
GIVE UP THAT EASILY!

02:25.395 --> 02:27.397
WE JUST NEED TO MOVE
OUR CONCERT.

02:27.480 --> 02:29.065
WHAT DO YOU SAY,
CRITTERS?

02:29.149 --> 02:31.359
I DON'T KNOW, NELLA.

02:31.442 --> 02:34.028
{\an1}YEAH, THAT ORC
REALLY SCARED US.

02:34.112 --> 02:35.238
COME ON!

02:35.321 --> 02:36.447
{\an5}WE'VE PRACTICED
TOO HARD TO
GIVE UP NOW!

02:36.531 --> 02:38.741
AND BESIDES,

02:38.825 --> 02:41.870
I KNOW THE PERFECT PLACE
FOR A CONCERT.

02:41.953 --> 02:43.246
{\an1}YOU DO?

02:43.329 --> 02:44.414
{\an3}WHERE?

02:44.497 --> 02:46.416
SOMEPLACE FABULOUS!

02:46.499 --> 02:49.961
EVEN MORE FABULOUS THAN
A CONCERT IN THE WOODS?

02:50.044 --> 02:51.671
YEP. EVEN MORE.

02:51.754 --> 02:53.673
WE'RE GOING TO HAVE
A ROYAL CONCERT

02:53.756 --> 02:56.050
AT THE CASTLE!

02:57.010 --> 02:58.636
[ROYAL FANFARE]

02:58.720 --> 02:59.888
NELLA: HELLO!

02:59.971 --> 03:00.930
AND WELCOME BACK
TO THE FIRST ANNUAL

03:01.014 --> 03:04.767
ROYAL CONCERT
AT THE CASTLE!

03:04.851 --> 03:06.352
[APPLAUSE]

03:06.436 --> 03:08.396
NOW--UM, WHERE WERE WE?

03:08.479 --> 03:09.439
OH, YEAH.

03:09.522 --> 03:11.441
TRINKET, IF YOU PLEASE?

03:11.524 --> 03:13.192
[PITCH PIPE PLAYING]

03:13.276 --> 03:15.570
ALL: ♪ WE SING THIS-- ♪

03:15.653 --> 03:17.864
ORC: GAAH-BLAAA-BLAAA!

03:17.947 --> 03:19.032
TRINKET: THE ORC!

03:19.115 --> 03:21.075
HE'S BACK!

03:21.159 --> 03:23.286
WHY DOES THIS
ALWAYS HAPPEN?

03:23.369 --> 03:25.455
WHAT'S THE ORC
DOING HERE?!

03:25.538 --> 03:27.081
[ORC HOWLING]

03:27.165 --> 03:29.792
{\an1}LOOKS LIKE NOWHERE
IS SAFE TO SING!

03:29.876 --> 03:30.627
CONCERT CANCELED!

03:30.710 --> 03:33.296
CANCELED, I SAY!

03:33.379 --> 03:34.130
THIS CAN'T BE HAPPENING.

03:34.213 --> 03:37.258
EVERYONE'S WORKED SO HARD,

03:37.342 --> 03:39.719
AND WE WERE SO EXCITED
FOR THE CONCERT.

03:39.802 --> 03:42.472
IT'S--IT'S JUST NOT RIGHT.

03:42.555 --> 03:44.098
MY HEART IS BRIGHT!

03:44.182 --> 03:46.100
TIME TO BE A PRINCESS KNIGHT!

03:46.184 --> 03:47.060
♪ MY HEART GROWS STRONG ♪

03:47.143 --> 03:49.479
♪ IT'S TIME TO SHINE MY LIGHT ♪

03:49.562 --> 03:51.606
♪ SWORD, SHIELD, BOOTS ♪

03:51.689 --> 03:53.566
♪ MY COURAGE SHINING BRIGHT ♪

03:53.650 --> 03:57.779
♪ NOW I AM
THE PRINCESS KNIGHT ♪

03:59.155 --> 04:02.450
{\an1}NOW, THAT'S A KNIGHT
IN SHINING ARMOR!

04:05.745 --> 04:07.455
WOW!

04:07.538 --> 04:08.998
SHE'S GREAT.

04:09.582 --> 04:12.126
BLAA-OOH!

04:13.336 --> 04:15.088
GAAH-BAAA-BLAAH!

04:16.422 --> 04:17.839
OOH-BAAA-BAAA-GAAH!

04:17.923 --> 04:18.257
OOH!

04:20.677 --> 04:21.886
HUH?!

04:21.970 --> 04:23.429
AHH-BAA-BAA-BAAH?

04:23.513 --> 04:25.390
{\an1}SHE'S NOT GREAT,
SHE'S THE GREATEST!

04:25.473 --> 04:29.936
{\an4}NOW I'M GONNA
GIVE THAT ORC
A GOOD TALKING TO!

04:30.019 --> 04:32.105
[HOWLING]

04:32.188 --> 04:35.400
{\an1}ACTUALLY, MAYBE YOU SHOULD
HANDLE THIS, NELLA.

04:36.567 --> 04:37.360
UH, HI THERE.

04:37.443 --> 04:40.279
{\an1}I'M NELLA,
THE PRINCESS KNIGHT.

04:40.363 --> 04:41.656
OH. HELLO, NELLA.

04:41.739 --> 04:44.117
I'M, UH, TRAPPED.

04:44.200 --> 04:47.370
{\an4}I'M CLOD, AND THIS
IS MY BEST FRIEND
SIR GARRETT.

04:47.453 --> 04:48.538
HI, TRAPPED.

04:48.621 --> 04:49.872
OH, NO, NO, NO.

04:49.956 --> 04:52.000
NO, MY NAME IS GORK.

04:52.083 --> 04:54.669
BUT I AM TRAPPED
IN WHAT LOOKS LIKE

04:54.752 --> 04:57.255
SOME VERY COLORFUL
RIBBONS.

04:57.338 --> 04:59.424
{\an1}YEAH, SORRY
ABOUT THAT, GORK.

04:59.507 --> 05:02.635
IT'S JUST YOU WERE
SCARING EVERYONE.

05:02.719 --> 05:03.469
I WAS?

05:03.553 --> 05:06.389
OHH.

05:06.472 --> 05:11.019
{\an5}IS THAT WHY THEY WERE
RUNNING AWAY FROM ME,
SCREAMING?

05:11.102 --> 05:13.980
{\an1}THAT'S KIND OF WHAT HAPPENS
WHEN YOU HOWL AT PEOPLE.

05:14.063 --> 05:16.399
WHEN I WHAT AT PEOPLE?

05:16.482 --> 05:17.442
OH, YOU KNOW...

05:17.525 --> 05:20.111
[IMITATES GORK]

05:20.194 --> 05:21.195
{\an1}HOWL.

05:21.279 --> 05:24.657
THAT WASN'T
HOWLING!

05:24.741 --> 05:26.743
THAT'S HOW I
SING!

05:26.826 --> 05:28.578
ALL: REALLY?

05:28.661 --> 05:31.080
REALLY!

05:31.164 --> 05:32.081
{\an1}OOH.

05:32.165 --> 05:32.957
THIS IS AWKWARD.

05:33.041 --> 05:35.918
I HEARD
YOUR CONCERT,

05:36.002 --> 05:37.253
AND THE SINGING
WAS SO PRETTY,

05:37.336 --> 05:41.257
{\an5}AND I--I WANTED
TO BE IN THE
CHORUS, TOO,

05:41.340 --> 05:44.635
BUT NOBODY LIKES
MY ORC SINGING!

05:44.719 --> 05:45.762
OOH!

05:45.845 --> 05:47.305
OH, DON'T CRY, GORK.

05:47.388 --> 05:50.308
{\an4}WE DIDN'T REALIZE
YOU WANTED TO BE
A PART OF OUR CHORUS.

05:50.391 --> 05:52.101
YOU CAN JUST JOIN US.

05:52.185 --> 05:53.311
NO.

05:53.394 --> 05:56.230
I CAN'T SING LIKE
YOU GUYS.

05:56.314 --> 05:57.523
[SNIFFLING]

05:57.607 --> 05:58.483
HMM. WELL...

05:58.566 --> 06:01.944
{\an1}MAYBE WE CAN GIVE YOU
SINGING LESSONS!

06:02.028 --> 06:03.112
YEAH!

06:03.196 --> 06:05.948
{\an1}YOU KNOW, I LEARNED TO SING
FROM MY GRANDMOTHER...

06:06.032 --> 06:08.284
{\an1}LEAD ALTO AT THE
METROPOL-ICORN OPERA.

06:08.367 --> 06:10.578
VERY FAMOUS.
NO BIG DEAL.

06:10.661 --> 06:12.580
{\an1}I'D BE HAPPY
TO TEACH YOU, GORK.

06:12.663 --> 06:13.748
[SNIFFLING]

06:13.831 --> 06:14.290
REALLY?

06:14.373 --> 06:16.250
YOU WOULD DO THAT?

06:16.334 --> 06:19.378
{\an1}I HAVE A GIFT,
I SHOULD SHARE IT.

06:19.462 --> 06:21.839
AWW, THAT'S SO NICE
OF YOU, TRINK.

06:21.923 --> 06:23.299
WE'LL PRACTICE
WITH GORK,

06:23.382 --> 06:25.051
AND HE CAN JOIN US
IN OUR CONCERT.

06:25.134 --> 06:26.302
AWESOME!

06:26.385 --> 06:27.595
[CHEERING]

06:27.678 --> 06:29.680
{\an1}PLEASE!
QUIET, CHORUS.

06:29.764 --> 06:32.600
WE HAVE WORK TO DO.

06:37.855 --> 06:39.607
NOW,
LIKE THIS...

06:39.690 --> 06:42.026
♪ MI-MI-MI-MI-
MI-MI-MEEE ♪

06:42.110 --> 06:44.821
♪ BLA-BLEE-BLEE-
BLAAAHHH ♪

06:44.904 --> 06:45.988
AWESOME!

06:46.072 --> 06:48.282
WE HEARD
THE DRAGON!

06:48.366 --> 06:49.700
WE'LL SAVE YOU!

06:49.784 --> 06:50.326
OH, IT'S OK.

06:50.409 --> 06:51.410
WE WERE JUST SINGING.

06:51.494 --> 06:56.082
{\an1}SO THERE'S NO DRAGON
WITH A TUMMY ACHE?

06:56.165 --> 06:58.626
{\an1}BACK IT UP, FELLAS.
FALSE ALARM.

06:58.709 --> 07:00.545
JUST AN ORC SINGING.

07:00.628 --> 07:02.380
OHH.

07:04.048 --> 07:08.636
♪ LET'S TRY SINGING
HIGH UP HERE ♪

07:08.719 --> 07:10.638
♪ BLAA-BLEE-BLEE-
GAAH-BLAAH ♪

07:10.721 --> 07:13.850
♪ RRRHHHEEEAAAA ♪

07:17.645 --> 07:20.565
MAYBE YOU COULD TRY
SINGING WHILE YOU SPIN!

07:20.648 --> 07:22.733
♪ LA-LA-LA-LA-LA-LA-
LA-LA-LAAA ♪

07:22.817 --> 07:24.443
♪ GRAH-BLAA-BLAA-- ♪

07:24.527 --> 07:26.237
OHH-AHH-AHH-OOP!

07:27.655 --> 07:28.865
OH, THAT'S IT!

07:28.948 --> 07:31.534
[GORK SOBS]

07:31.617 --> 07:32.869
I GIVE UP!

07:32.952 --> 07:34.745
I CAN'T SING
LIKE YOU...

07:34.829 --> 07:37.123
OR YOUR REALLY
FASHIONABLE UNICORN.

07:37.206 --> 07:40.209
SO I'LL JUST GO HOME,

07:40.293 --> 07:43.212
AND I'LL NEVER EVER
SING AGAIN!

07:43.296 --> 07:44.589
[CRYING]

07:47.300 --> 07:50.803
GORK IS
REALLY UPSET.

07:50.887 --> 07:54.682
OHH, I CAN'T STAND
TO SEE AN ORC CRY.

07:54.765 --> 07:55.224
ME NEITHER.

07:55.308 --> 07:58.060
HE TRIED SO HARD.

07:58.144 --> 08:01.189
AND HE CALLED ME
FASHIONABLE.

08:01.272 --> 08:03.816
{\an1}GUESS THAT'S A NEW FACT
TO PUT ON THE CARD:

08:03.900 --> 08:06.611
"ORCS CAN ONLY SING
IN THEIR OWN WAY."

08:06.694 --> 08:07.778
WAIT! THAT'S IT!

08:07.862 --> 08:11.073
{\an5}WE'RE TRYING
TO GET GORK
TO SING LIKE US,

08:11.157 --> 08:13.743
BUT WE ALL SING IN
OUR OWN WAY, TOO!

08:13.826 --> 08:15.578
WE DO?

08:13.826 --> 08:15.578
{\an1}REALLY?

08:15.661 --> 08:17.496
{\an5}YOU DON'T SAY?

08:15.661 --> 08:17.496
THINK ABOUT IT.

08:17.580 --> 08:20.041
FIDGET, YOU SING
REALLY, REALLY HIGH.

08:20.124 --> 08:21.167
{\an1}I DO!

08:21.250 --> 08:21.959
AND, TILLY,

08:22.043 --> 08:23.753
{\an1}YOU SING
REALLY, REALLY LOW.

08:23.836 --> 08:24.879
FOR SURE!

08:24.962 --> 08:28.424
AND, FIZZLE, YOU JUST
SQUAWK LIKE A...A...

08:28.507 --> 08:31.260
A WILD HORNBILLED
FEATHERFLAPPER!

08:31.344 --> 08:32.470
[SQUAWKS]

08:32.553 --> 08:33.971
RIGHT, BUT WE
FOUND A WAY TO PUT

08:34.054 --> 08:36.097
{\an5}EVERYONE'S SOUND
TOGETHER IN
OUR OWN CHORUS.

08:36.182 --> 08:38.351
♪ IT'S TRUE ♪

08:38.433 --> 08:39.434
♪ TRUE ♪

08:39.519 --> 08:40.727
{\an1}♪ TRUE ♪

08:40.811 --> 08:43.147
SEE? WE DON'T NEED
TO CHANGE GORK.

08:43.231 --> 08:46.442
WE NEED HIM TO STAY
EXACTLY THE WAY HE IS.

08:46.525 --> 08:47.735
SMART GIRL!

08:46.525 --> 08:47.735
YOU SAID IT!

08:47.818 --> 08:48.819
COME ON! WE'VE GOT
TO FIND HIM!

08:48.903 --> 08:50.988
{\an1}HEH HEH!

08:51.072 --> 08:53.574
{\an1}I DON'T THINK THAT'LL
BE A PROBLEM.

08:53.658 --> 08:56.744
[GORK CRYING LOUDLY]

08:58.287 --> 08:59.330
[CRYING]

08:59.413 --> 09:00.581
[SPLOSH]

09:00.665 --> 09:02.291
HE'S HEADED DOWN THE HILL!

09:03.042 --> 09:06.295
[CRYING]

09:06.379 --> 09:07.713
GARRETT: OH, NO!

09:07.797 --> 09:10.132
HE'S LOCKED HIMSELF
IN HIS TREE STUMP

09:10.216 --> 09:12.635
WAY DOWN AT THE BOTTOM
OF THE HILL.

09:12.718 --> 09:14.470
BUT HOW ARE WE
GONNA GET DOWN?

09:14.553 --> 09:15.930
IT'S SO MUDDY.

09:16.013 --> 09:19.725
{\an1}AND HAVE YOU EVER SEEN WHAT MUD
DOES TO RUBY HORSESHOES?

09:19.809 --> 09:22.979
{\an1}DON'T WORRY, TRINK.
I'VE GOT AN IDEA.

09:24.397 --> 09:25.564
HOP ON, EVERYONE!

09:25.648 --> 09:27.108
GARRETT: WHOO-HOO!

09:27.191 --> 09:28.651
[LAUGHTER]

09:28.734 --> 09:30.778
GARRETT: WHOA!

09:30.861 --> 09:32.530
AWESOME!

09:33.739 --> 09:35.658
TRINKET: YEAH!

09:35.741 --> 09:37.493
{\an5}GOOD THINKING,
NELLA!
WE MADE IT!

09:37.576 --> 09:39.954
{\an4}YEAH, BUT WE STILL
HAVE TO GET GORK
TO COME OUT.

09:40.037 --> 09:40.997
[KNOCKING]

09:41.080 --> 09:43.165
NELLA: GORK?

09:43.249 --> 09:44.667
GORK?

09:44.750 --> 09:46.460
GORK: GO AWAY!

09:46.544 --> 09:48.587
GORK, PLEASE COME OUT.

09:48.671 --> 09:50.464
WE NEED YOU FOR OUR CONCERT.

09:50.548 --> 09:52.591
GORK: NO, NO, YOU DON'T.

09:52.675 --> 09:55.344
{\an5}I CAN'T SING LIKE YOU
AND YOUR CRITTER CHORUS,
REMEMBER?

09:55.428 --> 09:59.682
{\an1}I KNOW...THAT'S WHY
WE NEED YOU.

09:59.765 --> 10:02.893
{\an1}♪ WE LOVE YOUR SWEET
"GA-BLAHHH" ♪

10:02.977 --> 10:05.521
♪ HOW YOU SING
"BLOOGH-BLEEE" ♪

10:05.604 --> 10:08.941
{\an1}♪ OUR SONG'S
NOT COMPLETE ♪

10:09.025 --> 10:11.944
♪ WITHOUT YOU
AND YOU AND YOU ♪

10:12.028 --> 10:14.196
♪ AND MEEE ♪

10:15.448 --> 10:17.700
ALL: ♪ WE LOVE YOUR HIGH
"GA-BLAHHH" ♪

10:19.785 --> 10:21.746
♪ EVEN YOUR LOW
"BLOOGH-BLEEE" ♪

10:21.829 --> 10:27.001
GARRET AND CLOD:
♪ YOU SING THE WAY YOU DOOO ♪

10:27.084 --> 10:28.961
♪ AND I SING LIKE... ♪

10:29.045 --> 10:31.881
♪ ME-ME-ME-ME-
ME-ME-ME-MEEE ♪

10:31.964 --> 10:34.008
ALL: ♪ WE LOVE YOUR SWEET
"GA-BLAHHH" ♪

10:34.091 --> 10:35.384
♪ HOW YOU SING
"BLOOGH-BLEEE" ♪

10:35.468 --> 10:39.347
{\an1}♪ OUR SONG'S NOT COMPLETE
WITHOUT YOU AND YOU AND YOU ♪

10:39.430 --> 10:42.350
♪ AND MEEE ♪

10:42.433 --> 10:46.145
ALL: ♪ WE LOVE YOUR SWEET
"GA-BLAHHH" ♪

10:46.228 --> 10:50.107
♪ HOW YOU SING
"BLOOGH-BLEEE" ♪

10:50.191 --> 10:52.443
♪ OUR SONG'S NOT COMPLETE ♪

10:52.526 --> 10:56.864
♪ WITHOUT YOU AND YOU AND YOU ♪

10:56.947 --> 10:58.741
♪ AND MEEE ♪

10:58.824 --> 11:01.243
GORK: ♪ OOH-BLAAAG-GLEEE ♪

11:01.327 --> 11:02.411
[APPLAUSE]

11:02.495 --> 11:03.621
THEY LIKE ME!

11:03.704 --> 11:05.706
THEY REALLY
LIKE ME!

11:05.790 --> 11:06.916
THANK YOU!

11:06.999 --> 11:08.334
THANK YOU!

11:08.417 --> 11:11.879
{\an1}HEY, UH,
CAN I GET A BITE?

11:11.962 --> 11:13.798
[LAUGHTER]

11:17.843 --> 11:19.970
{\an8}"THE BLAINE GAME."

11:20.846 --> 11:23.099
LET'S PLAY
FOLLOW THE KNIGHT!

11:23.182 --> 11:24.392
{\an1}HUP! WHOA!

11:24.475 --> 11:27.686
{\an1}FOLLOW THE KNIGHT!
YEAH!

11:27.770 --> 11:29.939
TURN, DODGE, LUNGE!

11:30.022 --> 11:31.607
{\an1}AWESOME KNIGHT MOVES,
NELLA!

11:31.690 --> 11:33.943
TURN, DODGE, LUNGE!

11:34.026 --> 11:35.111
HA HA!
NOW SPIN!

11:35.194 --> 11:37.113
WHOO!

11:37.196 --> 11:40.324
WHOA-OH-OH!

11:40.408 --> 11:41.200
{\an3}WHOA!

11:41.283 --> 11:42.743
COME ON, GARRETT.

11:42.827 --> 11:46.288
{\an1}LET'S GIVE THOSE
KNIGHT MOVES ANOTHER TRY.

11:46.372 --> 11:47.415
DID SOMEONE SAY
"KNIGHT MOVES"?

11:47.498 --> 11:51.210
THAT CALLS FOR
A KNIGHT LIKE ME!

11:51.293 --> 11:52.628
TURN, DODGE, LUNGE, PARRY,

11:52.711 --> 11:54.255
{\an1}OVER THE SHOULDER,
UNDER THE LEG,

11:54.338 --> 11:56.924
LUNGE, LUNGE, LUNGE,

11:57.007 --> 11:58.342
{\an1}AND HA-HA!

11:58.426 --> 12:01.095
{\an1}I WIN, AND, OH, BOY,
WAS THAT EASY,

12:01.178 --> 12:02.304
{\an1}BECAUSE WHEN IT COMES
TO DOING KNIGHTLY THINGS,

12:02.388 --> 12:04.098
THIS KNIGHT
ALWAYS WINS.

12:04.181 --> 12:07.435
{\an5}WELL, THIS GAME'S
NOT REALLY ABOUT
WINNING, SIR BLAINE.

12:07.518 --> 12:09.645
{\an5}COME ON, ADMIT IT!

12:07.518 --> 12:09.645
HA HA!

12:09.728 --> 12:13.065
OK. YOU WON THAT ONE,
SIR BLAINE.

12:13.149 --> 12:14.817
LET'S KEEP PLAYING,
YOU GUYS.

12:14.900 --> 12:16.402
FOLLOW THE KNIGHT!

12:16.485 --> 12:17.987
{\an5}FOLLOW THE KNIGHT!

12:16.485 --> 12:17.987
FOLLOW THE KNIGHT!

12:18.070 --> 12:22.074
[LAUGHTER]

12:22.158 --> 12:22.867
HA-HA!
I WIN!

12:22.950 --> 12:25.119
{\an5}I WIN!
I WIN!
I WIN!

12:25.202 --> 12:26.203
I'M
THE BEST!

12:26.287 --> 12:28.205
BLAINE,
YOU HEARD NELLA.

12:28.289 --> 12:29.999
THE GAME'S
NOT ABOUT WINNING.

12:30.082 --> 12:32.001
{\an5}YOU'RE JUST
SAYING THAT
BECAUSE I WON.

12:32.084 --> 12:34.086
COME ON! FOLLOW
THE KNIGHT!

12:34.170 --> 12:36.297
HUP! HUP! HOO! HUP!

12:36.380 --> 12:38.299
HEY, THAT LOOKS LIKE FUN!

12:38.382 --> 12:39.633
{\an1}HUP!

12:39.717 --> 12:40.259
HUP! HUP!

12:40.342 --> 12:42.761
WATCH THIS.

12:42.845 --> 12:43.804
UHH!

12:43.888 --> 12:44.972
WHOA-WHOA-WHOA!

12:45.055 --> 12:46.265
[CRASH]

12:46.348 --> 12:48.476
{\an5}YOU OK, BLAINE?

12:46.348 --> 12:48.476
{\an1}OF COURSE.

12:48.559 --> 12:51.437
{\an4}I ONLY TRIPPED BECAUSE
THAT CLOUD BLOCKED OUT
THE SUNLIGHT.

12:51.520 --> 12:52.062
[GASPING]

12:52.146 --> 12:53.731
THAT'S NO CLOUD.

12:53.814 --> 12:54.732
THAT'S A...

12:54.815 --> 12:56.692
ALL: DRAGON!

12:56.775 --> 12:58.319
GARRETT: AWESOME!

12:58.402 --> 12:59.111
KING: OH, YOU DON'T SAY!

12:59.195 --> 13:01.363
OH, I CAN'T
BELIEVE IT!

13:01.447 --> 13:03.365
{\an5}I'VE NEVER SEEN
A DRAGON THAT LOOKED
LIKE THAT BEFORE!

13:03.449 --> 13:07.244
{\an4}THAT'S BECAUSE IT'S
A PINK POLKA-DOTTED
MOUNTAIN DRAGON, SWEETIE.

13:07.328 --> 13:09.497
A WHAT?

13:09.580 --> 13:11.540
{\an1}A PINK POLKA-DOTTED
MOUNTAIN DRAGON, NELLA!

13:11.624 --> 13:14.585
IF I MAY,
YOUR MAJESTY, SIR?

13:14.668 --> 13:17.046
{\an1}ACCORDING TO MY
KNIGHTLY TRADING CARDS,

13:17.129 --> 13:20.966
{\an1}THE DRAGON IS BIG
WITH PINK POLKA DOTS, AND...

13:21.050 --> 13:22.218
{\an1}[GASPING]

13:22.301 --> 13:24.720
{\an1}NOBODY HAS EVER SEEN
ONE OF ITS EGGS HATCH BEFORE!

13:24.803 --> 13:27.181
THAT'S RIGHT,
SIR GARRETT.

13:27.264 --> 13:28.224
AND THE FIRST KNIGHT
TO SEE IT HATCH

13:28.307 --> 13:32.061
{\an5}WILL BE AWARDED
A SPECIAL
DRAGON MEDAL!

13:32.144 --> 13:34.063
BLAINE: WHOA!

13:34.146 --> 13:35.731
THEN I SHALL TOTALLY

13:35.814 --> 13:37.066
BE THAT
KNIGHT!

13:37.149 --> 13:37.900
{\an5}WHEN IT
COMES
TO SEEING

13:37.983 --> 13:40.319
{\an5}PINK
POLKA-DOTTED
DRAGON EGGS

13:40.402 --> 13:42.404
HATCH, I'M
THE BEST!

13:42.488 --> 13:45.115
{\an5}I'D LOVE TO SEE
THAT DRAGON EGG
HATCH.

13:45.199 --> 13:45.950
I BET
IT'S AMAZING!

13:46.033 --> 13:47.451
WELL, YOU CAN
TRY IF YOU WANT,

13:47.535 --> 13:50.746
BUT I'M
GONNA WIN!

13:50.829 --> 13:52.748
{\an5}WINNING
WOULD
BE COOL,

13:52.831 --> 13:54.833
{\an5}BUT SEEING
THAT EGG
HATCH

13:54.917 --> 13:56.877
WOULD BE
THE COOLEST!

13:56.961 --> 13:58.837
YOU'RE ON, SIR BLAINE!

13:58.921 --> 14:00.381
MY HEART IS BRIGHT!

14:00.464 --> 14:02.258
TIME TO BE A PRINCESS KNIGHT!

14:02.341 --> 14:04.385
♪ MY HEART GROWS STRONG ♪

14:04.468 --> 14:05.928
♪ IT'S TIME TO SHINE MY LIGHT ♪

14:06.011 --> 14:07.930
♪ SWORD, SHIELD, BOOTS ♪

14:08.013 --> 14:08.931
♪ MY COURAGE SHINING BRIGHT ♪

14:09.014 --> 14:14.395
♪ NOW I AM
THE PRINCESS KNIGHT ♪

14:15.020 --> 14:16.897
THAT'S OUR GIRL!

14:16.981 --> 14:18.232
{\an1}MM-HMM!

14:18.315 --> 14:20.609
{\an1}THERE'S JUST ONE QUESTION:
HOW DO YOU FIND THE NEST

14:20.693 --> 14:23.445
OF A PINK POLKA-DOTTED
MOUNTAIN DRAGON?

14:23.529 --> 14:24.822
I BELIEVE I CAN BE
OF SOME ASSISTANCE.

14:24.905 --> 14:29.785
{\an1}YOU SEE, NELLA, PINK
POLKA-DOTTED DRAGONS LIVE...

14:29.868 --> 14:31.912
{\an1}ON PINK POLKA DOT
MOUNTAIN!

14:31.996 --> 14:32.913
COME ON!

14:35.207 --> 14:37.334
SEE, THE PINK ROCKS

14:37.418 --> 14:39.378
KIND OF LOOK LIKE
POLKA DOTS.

14:39.461 --> 14:41.547
{\an1}AH. THE PINK POLKA-DOTTED
DRAGON'S NEST

14:41.630 --> 14:44.675
MUST BE RIGHT AT THE TOP.

14:44.758 --> 14:46.552
COME ON, GARRETT!

14:47.177 --> 14:49.305
{\an5}HA-HA!

14:47.177 --> 14:49.305
AH! BLAINE!

14:49.388 --> 14:50.764
WAIT, I'VE GOT
A JOKE!

14:50.848 --> 14:52.016
KNOCK-KNOCK.

14:52.099 --> 14:53.976
UH,
WHO'S THERE?

14:54.059 --> 14:54.476
BLAINE IS.

14:54.560 --> 14:56.812
BLAINE IS WHO?

14:56.895 --> 14:59.523
{\an5}BLAINE IS THE KNIGHT
WHO'S GONNA WIN
THIS CONTEST!

14:59.607 --> 15:01.609
{\an4}OK, BUT DON'T FORGET,
THE WHOLE POINT
OF THIS CONTEST

15:01.692 --> 15:04.445
{\an1}IS TO SEE
THE DRAGON EGG HATCH.

15:04.528 --> 15:06.822
OH, UM, THAT.

15:06.905 --> 15:08.616
YEAH, I GUESS.

15:08.699 --> 15:12.161
{\an1}♪ BLAINE, IT'S PLAIN
THAT YOU LOVE TO COMPETE ♪

15:12.244 --> 15:13.912
{\an1}♪ YOU FACE
EACH KNIGHTLY TASK ♪

15:13.996 --> 15:15.497
♪ LIKE A CONTEST ♪

15:15.581 --> 15:17.041
{\an5}♪ BUT DON'T FORGET
WHY WE'RE HAVING
THIS MATCH ♪

15:17.124 --> 15:19.793
♪ TO SEE AN AMAZING
DRAGON EGG HATCH ♪

15:19.877 --> 15:22.046
{\an5}♪ IT'S NOT JUST
WHO'S BETTER
OR BEST ♪

15:22.129 --> 15:23.839
{\an1}OR MAYBE YOU'RE SAYING THAT
BECAUSE I AM THE BEST.

15:23.922 --> 15:27.176
♪ I LEAP ROCKS
IN SINGLE BOUNDS ♪

15:27.259 --> 15:28.385
♪ 'CAUSE I'M THE BEST ♪

15:28.469 --> 15:30.179
♪ I CAN BENCH-PRESS 40 POUNDS ♪

15:30.262 --> 15:31.680
♪ 'CAUSE I'M THE BEST ♪

15:31.764 --> 15:34.516
♪ I CAN COUNT TO 32,
I CAN SING LIKE BIRDIES DO ♪

15:34.600 --> 15:36.268
♪ ALWAYS WINNING
AND DEFEATING ♪

15:36.352 --> 15:37.936
♪ 'CAUSE AT HAVING FUN
COMPETING ♪

15:38.020 --> 15:39.355
♪ I'M THE BEST ♪

15:39.438 --> 15:42.107
{\an5}BUT LET'S NOT FORGET
ABOUT SEEING THAT
DRAGON EGG.

15:42.191 --> 15:43.609
I WON'T...

15:43.692 --> 15:47.863
♪ 'CAUSE I'M THE BEEEST ♪

15:49.114 --> 15:50.366
{\an1}OH, NO!

15:50.449 --> 15:53.577
{\an1}HOW ARE WE EVER GONNA
GET ACROSS THAT?

15:53.661 --> 15:55.371
NELLA: I'M NOT SURE.

15:55.454 --> 15:56.413
MAYBE IF WE--

15:56.497 --> 15:59.083
♪ WATCH ME CROSS
THIS GIANT TRENCH ♪

15:59.166 --> 16:00.376
♪ 'CAUSE I'M THE BEST ♪

16:00.459 --> 16:01.710
♪ DID I MENTION
I SPEAK FRENCH? ♪

16:01.794 --> 16:02.711
♪ JE SUIS
LE MEILLEUR ♪

16:02.795 --> 16:05.339
THAT MEANS
"I'M THE BEST."

16:05.422 --> 16:06.715
♪ IN KNIGHTHOOD I WAS VERSED ♪

16:06.799 --> 16:08.676
{\an1}♪ AND I'LL SWING
ACROSS THERE FIRST ♪

16:08.759 --> 16:11.762
WHOA! EEE!

16:11.845 --> 16:12.805
♪ SEE? ♪

16:12.888 --> 16:13.681
♪ EVEN WHEN I'M
AT MY WORST ♪

16:13.764 --> 16:18.519
♪ I'M STILL THE BEEEST ♪

16:19.603 --> 16:22.106
AND THAT'S WHY I'M GONNA WIN!

16:22.189 --> 16:23.107
OH, YEAH?

16:23.190 --> 16:24.274
WELL, WE'RE THE BEST, TOO!

16:24.358 --> 16:26.735
OH!

16:26.819 --> 16:28.737
{\an5}IT'S GONNA BE
IMPOSSIBLE TO CATCH UP
WITH BLAINE NOW.

16:28.821 --> 16:31.865
NOT FOR A PRINCESS KNIGHT!

16:31.949 --> 16:33.909
I SEE A SHORTCUT.

16:37.246 --> 16:39.081
GREAT GAUNTLETS, NELLA!

16:39.164 --> 16:40.958
NOTHING CAN STOP YOU!

16:41.041 --> 16:42.126
AWW, THANKS.

16:47.506 --> 16:48.757
ALL RIGHT!
GO GET HIM, NELLA!

16:48.841 --> 16:51.093
OH, I'M NOT GOING ALONE.

16:51.176 --> 16:53.387
{\an1}YOU'RE GONNA SEE
THAT EGG TOO, GARRETT!

16:53.470 --> 16:54.555
{\an1}READY?

16:54.638 --> 16:57.266
{\an1}1, 2, 3...

16:54.638 --> 16:57.266
OHH!

16:57.349 --> 16:58.475
NELLA AND GARRETT: GO!

16:58.559 --> 17:00.728
WHOA-OH-OH!

17:00.811 --> 17:01.562
NELLA: WOW!

17:01.645 --> 17:04.440
{\an1}WHOA!
SIR BLAINE WAS SO WRONG.

17:04.522 --> 17:07.108
{\an1}HE'S NOT THE BEST,
YOU ARE, NELLA!

17:07.192 --> 17:07.776
AWW, THANKS, GARRETT.

17:07.859 --> 17:10.570
COME ON, LET'S HURRY!

17:14.867 --> 17:16.326
GARRETT: WHOA!

17:16.410 --> 17:16.868
NELLA: LOOK!

17:16.952 --> 17:18.704
THAT'S IT!

17:18.787 --> 17:21.832
THE PINK POLKA-DOTTED
DRAGON EGG!

17:21.915 --> 17:23.040
OH, MY GOSH!

17:23.125 --> 17:26.170
{\an1}AND IT'S EVEN MORE
BEAUTIFUL THAN I IMAGINED.

17:26.252 --> 17:27.588
{\an5}YEAH!

17:26.252 --> 17:27.588
OHH!

17:26.252 --> 17:27.588
{\an1}YIKES!

17:27.671 --> 17:29.214
BUT I WAS HERE FIRST.

17:29.298 --> 17:31.133
{\an1}LET'S HEAR IT
FOR SIR BLAINE!

17:31.216 --> 17:32.551
[IMITATES CHEERING]

17:32.634 --> 17:34.803
I WON! I WON!

17:34.887 --> 17:36.847
I SAW IT FIRST!
I SAW IT FIRST!

17:36.930 --> 17:39.349
{\an1}BUT YOU HAVEN'T EVEN
LOOKED AT IT YET!

17:39.433 --> 17:40.851
OR SEEN IT HATCH!

17:40.934 --> 17:43.562
{\an5}AND YOU HAVEN'T WON
UNTIL YOU'VE
SEEN IT HATCH.

17:43.645 --> 17:45.481
BUT I WILL SEE IT HATCH!

17:45.564 --> 17:47.274
{\an1}'CAUSE I'M AWESOME
SIR BLAINE!

17:47.357 --> 17:49.485
{\an1}I'M AWESOME,
AND I'M--WHOA!

17:49.568 --> 17:52.905
{\an3}OHH!

17:49.568 --> 17:52.905
[GASPING]

17:52.988 --> 17:54.490
{\an1}UH-OH.

17:54.573 --> 17:55.616
NELLA: OH, NO!

17:55.699 --> 17:57.284
COME ON!
STOP THAT EGG!

17:57.367 --> 18:01.163
{\an4}YEAH! I HAVE TO
SEE IT HATCH IF I
WANT TO WIN THE MEDAL!

18:02.831 --> 18:05.334
{\an1}WHOA!

18:05.417 --> 18:07.002
LET'S GO!

18:07.086 --> 18:08.629
{\an1}OH, YEAH!

18:13.091 --> 18:14.176
WHOA!

18:14.259 --> 18:15.385
GARRETT: WHOA-OH-OH!

18:15.469 --> 18:17.346
THIS IS AWESOME!

18:17.429 --> 18:18.305
{\an5}NELLA: WHOA!

18:17.429 --> 18:18.305
GARRETT: YEAH!

18:18.388 --> 18:19.681
WHOA!

18:19.765 --> 18:21.016
WE'RE GETTING CLOSE!

18:21.099 --> 18:24.102
{\an5}WE'VE GOT TO GET IT
BEFORE IT GOES OVER
THAT CLIFF!

18:24.186 --> 18:24.603
BLAINE: WHOA!

18:24.686 --> 18:26.939
I CAN GET IT!

18:27.022 --> 18:28.482
NO, BLAINE, WAIT!

18:28.565 --> 18:30.192
ALL: WHOA!

18:31.443 --> 18:31.735
NELLA: OH, NO!

18:31.819 --> 18:32.653
[SPLASH]

18:32.736 --> 18:34.530
COME ON! THIS WAY!

18:34.613 --> 18:37.282
[WATER RUSHING]

18:37.366 --> 18:38.909
NELLA: OH!

18:38.992 --> 18:39.868
[GARRETT GASPS]

18:39.952 --> 18:41.870
GARRETT: OH,
THAT'S NOT GOOD.

18:41.954 --> 18:45.332
{\an1}NELLA: WE'VE GOT TO STOP THAT
EGG BEFORE IT HITS THOSE ROCKS!

18:45.415 --> 18:47.709
{\an5}BUT HOW?

18:45.415 --> 18:47.709
BY WORKING TOGETHER!

18:47.793 --> 18:49.920
TOGETHER?
FORGET IT.

18:50.003 --> 18:51.213
THIS IS A CONTEST.

18:51.296 --> 18:54.383
{\an5}I STILL HAVE TO SEE
THAT EGG HATCH
IF I WANT TO WIN!

18:54.466 --> 18:56.385
WHAT DO WE DO,
NELLA?

18:56.468 --> 19:00.889
{\an5}IF THE ONLY WAY TO GET
BLAINE TO HELP US IS
TO MAKE THIS A CONTEST,

19:00.973 --> 19:02.057
THEN THAT'S WHAT WE'LL DO!

19:02.140 --> 19:04.726
{\an1}LAST ONE TO THOSE ROCKS
IS A SWAMP SLUG!

19:04.810 --> 19:07.563
YOU'RE ON!

19:08.313 --> 19:10.566
{\an1}DID IT!
SIR BLAINE DID IT!

19:10.649 --> 19:13.610
{\an5}BUT I BET
YOU CAN'T GET
TO THE OTHER SIDE.

19:13.694 --> 19:15.279
OH, YES, I CAN!

19:19.658 --> 19:22.119
I TOLD YOU SO!

19:22.202 --> 19:23.579
HURRY, NELLA!

19:23.662 --> 19:26.123
{\an1}IF THE EGG HITS THOSE ROCKS,
IT'LL BE SCRAMBLED!

19:26.206 --> 19:29.209
{\an1}THAT'S ALL PRETTY GOOD,
SIR BLAINE,

19:29.293 --> 19:34.214
{\an1}BUT LET'S SEE WHO'S THE BEST
AT RIBBON TUG OF WAR.

19:34.298 --> 19:34.882
YOU'RE ON!

19:34.965 --> 19:38.176
[NELLA AND BLAINE GRUNT]

19:39.928 --> 19:41.096
{\an1}ALL RIGHT!

19:41.179 --> 19:42.890
YOU STOPPED IT! WOW!

19:42.973 --> 19:45.475
{\an4}HA-HA!
WE SAVED THE EGG!
WE DID IT!

19:45.559 --> 19:47.477
{\an1}WAIT.

19:47.561 --> 19:48.478
"WE" DID IT?

19:48.562 --> 19:49.938
{\an1}WE?

19:48.562 --> 19:49.938
YEP!

19:50.022 --> 19:52.733
YOU GUYS WORKED
TOGETHER, BLAINE.

19:52.816 --> 19:54.776
{\an5}AND TOGETHER,
WE NEED TO GET THIS EGG
BACK TO ITS NEST

19:54.860 --> 19:57.821
SO WE CAN SEE IT HATCH.

19:57.905 --> 19:59.448
{\an1}DON'T WORRY. I'M SURE
I'LL THINK OF SOMETHING.

19:59.531 --> 20:01.408
[THUD]

20:01.491 --> 20:03.201
{\an3}GUYS?

20:03.285 --> 20:06.788
{\an5}WELL, WE'D BETTER DO IT
BEFORE THE MAMA DRAGON
COMES BACK.

20:06.872 --> 20:08.123
GUYS?

20:08.206 --> 20:10.500
{\an1}YEAH, WE WOULDN'T WANT TO BE
AROUND WHEN THAT DRAGON--

20:10.584 --> 20:12.628
[SCREAMING]

20:12.711 --> 20:16.048
UH, SORRY ABOUT THAT,
MRS. DRAGON.

20:16.131 --> 20:18.467
{\an8}WE DIDN'T MEAN
TO KNOCK YOUR EGG
OUT OF ITS NEST,

20:18.550 --> 20:21.136
BUT WE DID OUR BEST
TO KEEP IT SAFE.

20:22.387 --> 20:24.598
{\an4}OH, THAT'S OK.
THANK YOU FOR
TAKING CARE OF IT.

20:24.681 --> 20:28.560
{\an4}I'M JUST GLAD
SOMEONE WAS THERE
TO LOOK AFTER IT.

20:28.644 --> 20:30.729
{\an1}MY NAME'S POLKADOTTIE,
BY THE WAY.

20:30.812 --> 20:33.523
{\an8}OH, AND I'M NELLA,
THE PRINCESS KNIGHT.

20:33.607 --> 20:34.816
{\an8}NICE TO MEET YOU.

20:34.900 --> 20:37.486
{\an8}WELL, WE BETTER HEAD
BACK TO THE KINGDOM.

20:37.569 --> 20:39.988
OH, WHY DON'T I
GIVE YOU A RIDE.

20:40.072 --> 20:41.406
[CHEERING]

20:41.490 --> 20:43.283
{\an5}WHOA-HO-HO!

20:41.490 --> 20:43.283
WHOO-HOO!

20:43.367 --> 20:45.827
WOW!
SO COOL!

20:45.911 --> 20:47.454
WOW!

20:47.537 --> 20:48.664
AWESOME!

20:48.747 --> 20:49.665
{\an1}OOH, HEY, LOOK!
THERE'S THE KINGDOM!

20:49.748 --> 20:51.750
BLAINE: WOW!

20:51.833 --> 20:52.501
NELLA: COME ON, POLKADOTTIE!
DOWN THERE!

20:52.584 --> 20:54.586
[LAUGHTER]

20:54.670 --> 20:56.046
{\an1}OH, NO!

20:56.129 --> 20:56.880
RUN!

20:56.964 --> 20:58.507
{\an1}IT'S THAT
DRAGON AGAIN!

20:58.590 --> 20:58.966
[VILLAGERS CRY OUT]

20:59.049 --> 20:59.967
{\an1}HA HA HA!

21:00.050 --> 21:01.802
HEY, EVERYONE, IT'S OK.

21:01.885 --> 21:05.013
THIS IS MY NEW FRIEND...

21:05.097 --> 21:06.181
POLKADOTTIE.

21:06.264 --> 21:08.100
HELLO!
HOW DO YOU DO?

21:08.183 --> 21:09.685
{\an1}WOW! THE PINK POLKA-DOTTED
MOUNTAIN DRAGON!

21:09.768 --> 21:11.770
[GASPING]

21:11.853 --> 21:14.940
AND HER PINK
POLKA-DOTTED EGG!

21:15.023 --> 21:17.109
{\an5}THESE FINE YOUNG
KNIGHTS KEPT IT
SAFE AND SOUND,

21:17.192 --> 21:19.820
YOUR KINGLY
HIGHNESS, SIR.

21:19.903 --> 21:22.155
YOU SHOULD BE VERY PROUD.

21:22.239 --> 21:22.614
VERY PROUD.

21:22.698 --> 21:24.866
[CRACKING]

21:24.950 --> 21:25.283
OOH!

21:27.536 --> 21:28.286
{\an1}[GASPING]

21:30.288 --> 21:31.665
[BABBLING]

21:31.748 --> 21:33.542
